<TITLE>A Great REASON to Automate Root Cause Analysis</TITLE>

<!-- Date: Wednesday, August 28, 1996  2:37 PM -->

</HEAD>

<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUND="http://www.ercweb.com/SPECKLE.GIF">
<A NAME="Top"></A>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="http://www.ercweb.com/BCLOGO.GIF" HEIGHT=61 WIDTH=480 ALT="Beyond Compliance - September 1996"></CENTER>

<HR>
<CENTER><H1>A Great REASON to Automate Root Cause Analysis</H1></CENTER>
<CENTER><H5><A HREF="mailto:wsnell@ercweb.com">William Snell<BR>Vice-President</A></H5></CENTER>

<P>

<A HREF="REASSCR.HTM"><IMG SRC="REASON2.GIF" ALIGN=RIGHT ALT="Click here to view a sample screen"></A>If you are a safety, operations, or quality professional who is responsible for root cause problem-solving, then you should consider REASON. This Windows-based software is a powerful, expert system that guides you through the entire problem-solving process. It is designed to thoroughly identify all root causes, complete the investigation and analysis process quickly, and clearly document your work so that a decision can be made and implemented promptly.

<P>

REASON breaks down a problem into its essential parts, orders those parts into a logical model that can be measured, and then uses the results to help make informed decisions. Although most commonly used for accident investigation, REASON can be used on any business or operational problem:  a defective product, a severe laceration, a late delivery, a vehicle accident, a radioactive exposure, the loss of a valuable employee, a notice of violation received from a regulatory inspection, and more.

<P>
  
REASON can do this because it is a rule-based system, using a set of logic rules to guide the process. You do not have to know the rules because the expert system leads you through each step, then helps you verify the accuracy and completeness of your work.

<P>
 
For those environmental and safety professionals responsible for occurrence reporting, REASON provides a consistent and thorough analysis to identify both common deficiencies and prevention options. For those in Total Quality Management, REASON fulfills the "management by fact" mandates seen in the Malcom Baldridge Award and ISO 9000 certification.

<P>
 
Find out why manufacturers, chemical companies, refineries, nuclear plants, utilities, laboratories and more have turned to REASON when identifying root causes is critical.

<P>
 
REASON is delivered on either diskette or CD and sells for $895. Call 800-537-2372 to order Product Number 1200 today!

