<TITLE>CD-ROM Based Health and Safety Training is Finally Affordable</TITLE>

<!-- Date: Wednesday, August 21, 1996  11:16 AM -->

</HEAD>

<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUND="http://www.ercweb.com/SPECKLE.GIF">
<A NAME="Top"></A>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="http://www.ercweb.com/BCLOGO.GIF" HEIGHT=61 WIDTH=480 ALT="Beyond Compliance - September 1996"></CENTER>

<HR>
<CENTER><H1>CD-ROM Based Health and Safety Training is Finally Affordable</H1></CENTER>
<CENTER><H5><A HREF="mailto:wsnell@ercweb.com">William Snell<BR>Vice-President</A></H5></CENTER>

<P>

<IMG SRC="ODONNELL.GIF" BORDER=1 ALIGN=RIGHT>In the past, <I>Beyond Compliance</I> has documented the exciting growth in computer-based training (CBT) for compliance with safety and environmental regulations. We have detailed the benefits multimedia-based training can provide: on demand availability, self-paced learning, effective interaction (combining hearing, seeing, and doing), ability to capture and maintain student interest (through video, graphics, text and digital sound), improved retention, and automatic performance tracking.

<P>

