<A NAME="MIRSUpgraded"><HR></A>

<CENTER><H1>MIRS Software Upgraded</H1></CENTER>

<CENTER><H5>William Snell<br>
Vice President</h5></CENTER>

<IMG  SRC="Computer.GIF"  ALT="Computer" ALIGN=LEFT HEIGHT = 144 WIDTH =126>

A new and enhanced Material Inventory Report System (MIRS) version 3.4 was just announced and will be available in January. This easy-to-use, modular program offers automated solutions for SARA Title III reporting (including Tier I, Tier II, and Form R), MSDS management, CAA management, waste tracking, inventory tracking, NPDES, and state/local reporting.<P>
 
For the 1995 reporting year, there are a number of SARA Title III changes. EPA has added 286 chemicals to the TRI reportable chemicals list (there are now over 5,700 identified chemicals for the section 313 Form R alone). EPA also has made some important delisting decisions involving acetone and ammonium sulfate solution.<P>

MIRS software will keep you current every year <I>before</I>  the deadlines. You will also be one step ahead of EPA with thorough work sheets, audit trails, and multi-year reports.<P>

Whether you work on the latest Pentium workstation over a sophisticated network or on an older stand-alone DOS machine, there is a version of MIRS to meet your needs. The Windows version of MIRS is Windows `95 compatible and offers new features like automatic print driver compatibility, which is especially useful for network applications.<P>
 
Other MIRS features include read-only network access of company MSDS records, an expanded CAA module, a Chemical List Extension that has over 13,000 chemicals/categories, plus analysis and reporting capabilities of consolidated information with the Corporate MIRS module.<P>
 
MIRS continues to offer you the best set of tools for greatly simplifying your environmental compliance and safety data management responsibilities. To learn more or to request a demo, call 1-800-537-2372 or you may choose to <A HREF="DEMOS.HTM">download a demo here</A>.

<CENTER><IMG  SRC="Littlee.GIF" ALT="End"></CENTER><P>
<BR>
