<HR>
<CENTER><H1>MSDSs Are Now On CD-ROM</h1></CENTER>
<CENTER><h5>William Snell,<br>
Vice President</h5></CENTER>

<IMG  SRC="CD.GIF"  ALT="CD" ALIGN=LEFT>

There is a new reference for environmental, health and safety professionals that will change the way you think of Material Safety Data Sheets. Imagine how much file space it would take to hold over 162,000 MSDSs. Now imagine them all on two CD-ROMs. The MSDS Database on CD-ROM includes all products and chemicals purchased by the U. S. government that require material safety data sheets and is considered the largest and most comprehensive compilation of its kind in the world.<P>
Each MSDS record contains over 230 data fields, including:
<UL>
<LI>product identification data
<LI>general information
<LI>health hazard data
<LI>physical/chemical characteristics
<LI>fire and explosive hazard data
<LI>reactivity data
<LI>precautions for safe handling and use
<LI>control measures
<LI>disposal data
<LI>label data
<LI>ingredient data
<LI>record control data and more!
</UL>
<BR>

A complete search and retrieval engine is built-in, and information from the database may be sent to a printer or exported as either an ASCII or dBase file.<P>

The price for an annual subscription, which includes quarterly updates, is $325. Access over a local area network is available at no additional cost. In addition to using the database to locate MSDSs for the products you use today, you can also use it to find safer alternates, competitive products, or to find out the composition and hazards of products that you are considering for purchase. This thorough resource is an excellent value that you can order today by calling 1-800-537-2372 (ask for product #1255).<P>

