<head><title>US Army TRADOC Liaison Officers in the United Kingdom</title></head><body><IMG SRC="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/tradoccr.jpg"></IMG><h1><strong><i>US Army Training and Doctrine Command (TRADOC) </i></strong></h1><h2><strong>Liaison Officers in the United Kingdom</strong></h2><h3><strong><i>--- Where Tomorrow's Victories Begin ---</i></strong></h3><hr><p> <h2><strong>Mission</strong></h2><p> <ul> <li> Represent the Commanding General, TRADOC to the British Army and the British Ministry of Defence.<li> Represent the CG, TRADOC to US Army and Department of Defense activities in the United Kingdom.<li> Facilitate joint and combined warfare by presenting US Army needs and requirements to other US and allied military services. Monitor combat, doctrinal and training developments of other US and allied services that may affect or benefit the US Army.<li> Furnish combat development, doctrinal, training and educational information to appropriate MOD personnel. Assist in coordination with TRADOC action officers.<li> Examine technical developments from military and civilian sources for application to combat, doctrinal and training developments.<li> Provide response to requests for information in support of the TRADOC decision making process.<li> Provide assistance to US Army students and Personnel Exchange Program personnel in the United Kingdom, in coordination with US Army Attache, London.</ul><hr><h1><strong>Who we are, Where we are!</strong></h1><ul> <li><strong>Senior Liaison Officer - LTC(P) William M. Bransford</strong><ul><li>Trenchard Lines, Upavon, Wiltshire<li>with the Director General, Development and Doctrine (DGD&D)<li>telephone (UK-44) 1980-61-5060 / 5027 / fax 5209<li><a>To send an E-Mail, Click Here: <a href="mailto:wbransford@europe.dla.mil">wbransford@europe.dla.mil</a> </ul><p><li><strong>Training Liaison Officer - LTC Jim Lampkin</strong><ul><li>Combined Arms Training Centre (CATC), Warminster, Wiltshire<li>with the Commander of CATC<li>telepho