<H2>Funding Sources</H2><P><HR><P>


<I>Funding organization:</I> <B> Advanced Research and Projects Agency (ARPA)</B><BR>
<I>Location:</I> <B> </B><BR>
<I>Eligibility:</I><BR>
<I>Typical amounts:</I><BR>
<I>For more information, contact:</I>  Email: <B>;</B>  WWW: <B><A HREF="http://ftp.arpa.mil/">http://ftp.arpa.mil</A></B><BR>
<P>
<I>Funding organization:</I> <B> Air Force Office of Scientific Research (AFOSR)</B><BR>
<I>Location:</I> <B> </B><BR>
<I>Eligibility:</I><BR>
<I>Typical amounts:</I><BR>
<I>For more information, contact:</I>  Email: <B>;</B>  WWW: <B><A HREF="http://web.fie.com/web/fed/afr/">http://web.fie.com/web/fed/afr/</A></B><BR>
<P>
<I>Funding organization:</I> <B> European Office of Aerospace Research and Development (EOARD)</B><BR>
<I>Location:</I> <B> London, UK</B><BR>
<I>Eligibility:</I><BR>
<I>Typical amounts:</I><BR>
<I>For more information, contact:</I>  Email: <B>;</B>  WWW: <B><A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil">http://www.ehis.navy.mil</A></B><BR>

<P>
<I>Funding organization:</I> <B> International Science Foundation</B><BR>
<I>Location:</I> <B> Moscow, Russia</B><BR>
<I>Eligibility:</I><BR>
<I>Typical amounts:</I><BR>
<I>For more information, contact:</I>  Email: <B><A HREF="mailto:www-admin@isf.ru">www-admin@isf.ru</A>;</B>  WWW: <B><A HREF="http://www.isf.ru/">http://www.isf.ru/</A></B><P>

<I>Funding organization:</I> <B> Federal Government - Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR)</B><BR>
<I>Location:</I> <B> Florida, USA</B><BR>
<I>Eligibility:</I>US companies only<BR>
<I>Typical amounts:</I>up to $850,000<BR>
<I>For more information, contact:</I>  Email: <B><A HREF="mailto:list@seeport.com">list@seeport.com</A>;</B>  WWW: <B><A HREF="http://www.seeport.com/">http://www.seeport.com/</A></B><BR>

<P>
<I>Funding organization:</I> <B> US Civilian Research and Development Foundation for the Independent States of the FSU (CRDF)</B><BR>
<I>Location:</I> <B> Arlington, Virginia, USA</B><BR>
<I>Eligibility (brief outline):</I>  <B>Each proposal submitted must have one FSU Co-Investigator and one US Co-Investigator.  Each Co-Investigator must possess the degree of Ph D or the equivalent, have at least five scientific publications in the peer-reviewed scientific literature, and must work full-time in a civilian institution. FSU researchers must have been working in a defense related job.</B><BR>
<I>Typical amounts:</I>  <B>$40,000 for two years ($20,000/year).</B><BR>
<I>For more information, contact:</I> Address:  <B>US Civilian Research and Development Foundation, 1800 North Kent Street, Suite 1106, Arlington, Virginia 22209, USA;</B>  Tel. no.: <B>703/526-9720;</B>  Fax:  <B>703/526-9721;</B>  Email:  <B><A HREF="mailto:information@crdf.org">information@crdf.org</A></B>; WWW: <B><A HREF="http://www.crdf.inter.net">http://www.crdf.inter.net</A></B><BR><P>

This page was last updated on: 26 March 1996
