<H2>Conference Support Program (CSP) Guidelines</H2><HR><BR>

The Office of Naval Research Europe (ONR Europe) maintains scientific and technological liaison between U.S. naval research and development activities and scientific research establishments in Europe and the Middle East.  This liaison began in 1946 to expand scientific communication and continues to the present with beneficial results for all.  To assist in carrying out its liaison function, ONR Europe has limited funds for supporting various symposiums, conferences, and workshops held throughout Europe and the Middle East. Recent reductions in resources requires emphasis on topics of Navy Interest particularly small workshops with strong Navy program impact.  CSP does not generally support major meetings of international or national societies.  Rather, it supports the following types of scientific and technical meetings, usually at the instigation of ONREUR Science Officers:<P>

a.  Gatherings of invited international scientists and engineers specifically to discuss research of particular interest to Navy;<P>
	
b.  Topical or special focus sessions at larger international meetings, on aspects of the major theme that are of particular interest to Navy;<P>
	
c.  Workshops to develop papers describing the state of the art on specific topics in specific geographic regions, or to develop plans for research initiatives;<P>
	
d.  US access to international meetings not normally attended by US researchers;<P>
	
e.  Meetings between US and international scientists and engineers to discuss needs, compare programs and progress, and develop proposals for collaborations.<P>

As a condition of its support, ONREUR generally requires, free of additional cost, recognition of its sponsorship, a comprehensive written report of major events and conclusions suitable for distribution by ONREUR (within 30 days of the meeting), copies of all meeting materials, meeting space with audio visual support (if appropriate), and registration for a designated number of US participants.<P>

A request for CSP financial support should be in the form of a written proposal, signed and dated by a business official of the institution.  Organizations should submit proposals as soon as possible to allow sufficient time for reviews and for necessary correspondence to be completed for processing of payment of funds.<P>

<H3>Proposal Format</H3>

<B>1.  Title and Scope of Meeting:</B><BR> 
	<DD>Official Title, subtitle(s), and list of topics covered</DD><P>

<B>2.  Date of Meeting:</B><BR>
	<DD>Inclusive dates of meeting, and other pertinent dates such as deadlines for notification of support, and closing dates for abstracts, papers, and registration.</DD><P>

<B>3.  Objective and Content of Meeting:</B><BR>
	<DD><B>This section should provide enough information for the ONREUR Science Officer to assess relevance to Navy needs, and to identify the appropriate ONR Headquarters Program Officer for coordination and review if needed:</B></DD><BR>
<UL>
<LI>Describe the purpose of the meeting, and in particular of any specific session or workshop of special interest to ONR and the Navy. 
<LI>Discuss the theme or general topic of the meeting, the specific technical aspects or issues to be addressed for topics of particular interest to ONR, and what the meeting will contribute to science and technology in the field.
<LI>Describe the meeting format (e.g., plenary and breakout sessions, poster sessions, workshop, tour, hands-on experience with new techniques), and provide information on the program, including an agenda if available.
<LI>List the principal invited speakers and their title,  organization, and topics.  List any distinguished guests and their titles and organizations.
<LI>Describe expected meeting products (e.g., conference report, abstracts, book, plan, proposal). 
</UL>

<B>4.  Location of Meeting:</B><BR>
	<DD>Specific venue for the meeting, including city, country, street address, facility name, etc.  Include other pertinent logistic information such as recommended hotels and air, road and rail arrival sites.</DD><P>

<B>5.  Sponsor, Organizer, and Organizing Committee Members:</B><BR>
	<DD>Identify any sponsoring organization or institution, or the organization which has initiated the meeting and this request for CSP support.  Provide names, phone numbers, street and e-mail addresses of chair-persons, contact points, and organizing and programme committee members for all sessions.</DD><P>

<B>6.  Budget</B>
	<DD>Show total cost of the meeting.</DD><BR>
	<DD>Break out, by budget line item, costs (e.g., facilities, equipment, publications, technical support personnel, administrative support personnel, translation services,  travel) and income (e.g., registration fees, desired ONREUR support, and support from other organizations).</DD><BR>
	<DD>List other organizations being solicited for support, and the amount and type of support requested or approved.</DD><P>

<B>7.  ONREUR Support Requested</B><BR>
Specify the amount requested in US dollars, and the budget line items against which ONREUR support will be applied.<P>

<B>8.  Formal Statement of Acceptance of ONREUR Conditions</B><BR>
An appropriate official representative of the meeting must certify that the organizers will provide, free of additional charge:<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Recognition of ONREUR sponsorship in meeting literature;
<LI>A written summary of the meeting describing significant events, findings, or conclusions, to be distributed by ONREUR and placed on the ONREUR World Wide Web home page free of copyright or other restrictions, to be mailed to ONREUR no later than 30 days after the meeting;
<LI>Single copies of all materials that are provided in advance of or at the meeting, either free or for charge, to either prospective or actual recipients, including preliminary announcements, programs, collected abstracts,                                                                               agendas, etc., to be mailed to ONREUR no later than the time at which they are generally distributed; and
<LI>Three copies of all materials that are produced or compiled as a result of the meeting, such as proceedings, copies of all papers presented, or resultant books, to be mailed to ONREUR as soon as available.
</UL>

In addition, when applicable the official representative must also certify that the organizers will provide, free of additional charge:
<UL>
<LI>Appropriate meeting space and presentation support equipment for use by ONREUR representatives and other participants at the meeting; 
<LI>Other support as discussed with the cognizant ONREUR Science Officer; and
</UL>

A designated number or registration-free meeting places to be filled by scientists designated by ONREUR.<P> 

<B>Addresses and Phone Numbers for CSP Requests:</B><P>

Street Address and Mailing Address from Europe, Africa and the Middle East:<P>
	
	<DIR>Chief Scientist and Technical Director<BR>
	Office of Naval Research, Europe<BR>
	223 Old Marylebone Road<BR>
	London NW1 5TH, UK</DIR>


