</DOCHDR>
<H2>FASP Project</H2>

<H3>The aim</H3>

<UL>
<LI>Realizing the flexibility concepts of CIM architecture in the key area of the shipyard: the prefabrication
<LI>The final goal is the implementation of a demonstration model of a prefabrication workshop in which automatic robotized manufacturing lines are installed and integrated with the technical system (CAD-CAM) and with the production control system
</UL>

<H3>The partners</H3>

FINCANTIERI Italian shipbuilder - projeect leader<P>
ASTILLEROS ESPANOLES Spanish shipbuilder<P>
ANSALDO Italian electro-mechanical group<P>
ENEA Italian research Committee<P>
SOLVING Finnish air cushion transportation group<P>
IGM Austrian robot/welding company<P>

<H3>FASP Project slides</H3><P>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/phases.htm">The Phases</A><BR> 
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-2.htm">The Work Packages Subdivision</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-3.htm">Monfalcone Shipyard</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-4.htm">Plan</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-5.htm">Profiles Lane</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-6.htm">Subassemblies Line</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-7.htm">Assembly Station</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-8.htm">Robotized Welding Station</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-9.htm">Plate Bending Machine</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-10.htm">Curved Blocks Line</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-11.htm">Panel Line</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-12.htm">Flat Blocks Line</A><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/era10-13.htm">Robotized Welding Station</A><P>

     <H3>   Innovative system for the shipbuilding industry based on an
        integrated project to automate the prefabrication cycle</H3>
  
        Project description<BR>
        The research concerns an innovative system for the
        shipbuilding industry based on an integrated project to
        automate the prefabrication cycle.  The project covers
        fabrication, handling, fitting and welding operations of
        blocks up to 200 ton.  The project consists of three major
        phases which, starting from the analysis of the current
        system goes up to the implementation of innovative
        production systems in a pilot prefabrication shop within a
        FINCANTIERI shipyard.  The system envisages automatic cells
        and lines consisting of handling devices for heavy
        components up to 100 ton., robots and sensors for operation
        in non-structured environment, integrate control systems
        for CAD-CAM-CAPP, Real-Time scheduling as well as automatic
        quality control systems.<BR>
        Developments<BR>
        Considerable effort in applied research and integration of
        advanced technology is envisaged with special emphasis to
        be placed on the following:
 
<UL>
<LI>Automatic handling, positioning, clamping and welding systems for large and heavy parts
<LI>Robots for operation in non-structured environment
<LI>Sensors, vision systems and associated artificial intelligence programmes for operation in non-structured        environment.
<LI>Advanced CAD, CAM, CAPP and systems SW developments
<LI>Expert systems for workshop scheduling in a single lot production environment
<LI>Advanced man-machine interfaces and supervision system
</UL>





