<H3>Oct 92 - Sep 95<br>EUROPEAN NAVAL OCEANOGRAPHY<br><A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/stpierre.htm">David B. St.Pierre LCDR USN</A><br><I>Associate Director</I><br>Ocean, Atmosphere, and Space Science & Technology<p></H3><HR><P>
<B>an Office of Naval Research European Office newsletter</B><p><HR>
"European Naval Oceanography" reports on items of military interest in oceanography, meteorology, satellite remote sensing, undersea systems, and ocean engineering in Europe, Africa, and the Middle East. <p><p>Summary of Newsletter Titles are grouped as follows:<p><p>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="dstpsum.htm#remote">Remote Sensing of the Environment</A><p>
<LI><A HREF="dstpsum.htm#ocean">Oceanography/Meteorology Data & Modeling</A><p>
<LI><A HREF="dstpsum.htm#oceans">Ocean Systems</A><p>
<LI><A HREF="dstpsum.htm#prog">Programs, Plans, Policies, & Institutions</A><p>
<LI><A HREF="dstpsum.htm#europe">European Events</A><p>
<LI><A HREF="dstpsum.htm#misc">Miscellaneous</A>
</UL>
<p><p><p><p><p>

<H3><A NAME="remote">Remote Sensing of the Environment</A></H3><p><p>	
