<IMG SRC="http://www.ehis.navy.mil/50FIG9.GIF"><P>
      
Figure 9.  Symposium Attendees. L - R   A. Gargett, R. Barber, T. Halpern.<P>

<IMG SRC="http://www.ehis.navy.mil/50FIG10.GIF"><P>

Figure 10.  D. Krause discussing one of the poster papers with M. Serio (paper author) and another attendee.<P>

<IMG SRC="http://www.ehis.navy.mil/50FIG11.GIF"><P>
    
Figure 11.  Symposium Attendees. M. Roman (L) and L Clark <P>

<IMG SRC="http://www.ehis.navy.mil/50FIG12.GIF"><P>

Figure 12.  Symposium Attendees. A. Pierrot-Bults, Local Organizing Chair (L) and E. Van Den Kiren <P>
	

The Symposium continued with announcement of the 1996 selectee of TOSs <B>Walter Munk Medal</B> for Distinguished Research in Oceanography Related to Sound and the Sea (Fig 13). Dr. <B>James DeCorpo</B>, Head of ONRs Ocean, Atmosphere and Space Science and Technology Department discussed the background of this medal and the Navys support of it.  Dr. <B>Margaret Leinen</B>, outgoing President of TOS, announced the selectee, Dr. <B>Leonid Brekhovskikh</B> of Russia.  <P>

The Symposium concluded with cutting and sampling of a birthday cake commemorating the 50th anniversary of ONR (Fig 14).  Drs. Saalfeld, Dorman and Leinen closed the Symposium by  thanking all participants for attending and expressing wishes that this would launch an era of increased partnership between U.S. and European colleagues.  Symposium attendees then boarded the canal boats returning to the Okura Hotel.<P>

