<TITLE>ONREUR Support for U.S. Shipbuilding and Manufacturing</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P>

<H2>Subject:  Office of Naval Research Europe [ONREUR] Support for U.S. Shipbuilding and Manufacturing </H2>

<DD>	I am Howard M. Bunch, NAVSEA Professor of Ship Production Science and Research Scientist at the University of Michigan, Ann Arbor.  I have been given leave from the university to serve, for the next two years, as Associate Director, Manufacturing and Ship Production Sciences at the Office of Naval Research Europe, located in London, England.   My assignment is to monitor activities in Europe and Africa relating to manufacturing and ship production.    I will be concentrating on  technologies that enable manufacturing enterprises to become "world class"  by better design, construction, and sale of affordable commercial ships, and one-of-a-kind industrial products.  The information will  be passed on to U.S. manufacturers [especially shipyards] so they have insight in how to proceed in achieving their own  "world-class"  position.<P>
 
	<DD>One of the areas of especial focus will be the role of the vendor in the process.  It has become generally recognized that one of the most efficient production systems is a type that is extremely agile in its configuration; this agility is facilitated by the use of a vendor network that can be quickly configured for a specific product need. <P>

	<DD>A second focus area will be product/process modelling technology, including its utilization in marketing dynamics.  Computer hardware and software systems being introduced  for purposes of supporting flexible manufacturing systems will be of especial interest.<P>

	<DD>My plans are to issue a series of Manufacturing and Ship Production Newsletters.  They will document [1]the developmental status and potential impact of appropriate research and industrial process activities, [2] highlights of Europeqan technical conferences,  [3] trip reports  [to European shipyards, manufacturers, universities  and  research institutes], and [4] and points of contact for specific technical questions. Please confirm your interest in being included in the distribution of future newsletters.  [IF THERE IS NO RESPONSE, I WILL ASSUME THERE IS NO DESIRE FOR INCLUSION].  Additionally, your thoughts on specific interests would be appreciated. <P>

	<DD>Reports will be available via e-mail at my e-mail address or by regular mail.  They will also be available via the world wide web at the Office of Naval Research Europe home page, http://www.ehis.navy.mil/homepage/htm.  After entering the homepage, go to Newsletters: ONREUR[Professor Howard M. Bunch] <P>
	<DD>To date there have been three newsletters issued:<P>

	<DD><B>Newsletter #1</B>--Office of Naval Research Europe [ONREUR] Support
		for U.S. Shipbuilding and Manufacturing<BR>
	<DD><A HREF="hbnews2.htm"><B>Newsletter #2</B></A>--European Study Conferences on International Trade and
		Competition Law<BR>
	<DD><A HREF="hbnews3.htm"><B>Newsletter #3</B></A>--Listing of some conferences to be held in Europe during remainder of 1996 that might be of interest <BR>
<DD>to maritime industry management.<P>

	<DD>I shall also be pleased to be an informal information source on any queries you may have relative to my assignment area.  <P>


<B>International Address:</B><P>
       		
       		 <DD>Office of Naval Research Europe<BR>
      		  <DD>223 Old Marylebone Road<BR>
       		 <DD>London NW1 5TH England<BR>
       		 <DD>Telephone: 44-171-514-4942<BR>
       		 <DD>FAX: 44-171-723-6359<BR>
        		<DD>e-mail: hbunch@onreur.navy.mil<P>

<B>United States Mail Address:</B><P>

		<DD>Office of Naval Research Europe<BR>
		<DD>PSC 802, Box 39<BR>
		<DD>FPO AE 09499-0700<P>

