<HEAD>
<TITLE>European Study Conferences on International Trade and Competition Law</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P>
<H2>European Study Conferences on International Trade and Competition Law [Selected List]</H2>
<P><PRE>
Listed below is a selected list of conferences sponsored by European Study
Conferences, Ltd that might be of interest to senior management in the U.S. maritime 
industry.  For more information contact:

               Conference Secretariat
               ESC International Ltd
               565 Fulham Road
               London SW6 1ES, United Kingdom
               Tel: +44-171-386-9322
               FAX: +44-171-381-8914
</PRE><P><HR><P>
<H3>CROSS BORDER JOINT VENTURES CONFERENCE</H3><P>
<PRE><I>September, VIENNA                              &#163;350.00</I></PRE><P>
There are many ways in which a company can
expand into foreign markets, a joint venture being one of the
more popular ways.  This conference looks at the latest developments
and points out the pitfalls.  This will include coverage Central
and Eastern Europe.<P>
<H3>COMMERCIAL CONTRACTS IN THE EU</H3><P>
<PRE><I>4 day, various cities                             &#163;1100.00</I></PRE><P>
The basis of most business transactions is
a contractual relationship which is governed by a complex set
of rules developed over the years through decided cases, jurisprudence,
statutory enactments, codes and international conventions.  The
increase in international trade and business has added to this
complexity.  As contracts are such a basic element in business,
all those engaged in business operations, whatever their capacity,
need to have an understanding of the subject.  This event has
been specially designed to provide vital information on commercial
contracts in Europe, including the impact of EU law, for company
executives, businessmen and their professional advisers.  The
approach will be practical, allowing for questions and discussion.<BR>
Each regional centre will cover jurisdictions
in the neighbouring area.<BR>
The course will take place as follows:<P>

<B>June</B>  <BR>
BRUSSELS - Benelux Countries<BR>
<B>July</B><BR>
NICE - France, Italy, Spain, Portugal, Greece<BR>
<B>September</B><BR>
COPENHAGEN - Scandinavia;<BR>
MUNICH - Austria, Germany &amp; Switzerland<P>

<H3>ECONOMICS FOR THE COMPETITION LAWYER</H3>

<PRE><I>July, 1 day, LONDON                             &#163;350.00</I><P></PRE>

Competition Law can only be properly understood
in the context of the economic theories upon which it is based.
 This one day course will be presented by economists who are specialists
in competition matters - and will provide practising competition
lawyers with a practical insight into the economics of Competition
Law and the economic arguments which may be brought in infringement
proceedings.<P>

<H3>INTRODUCTION TO COMPETITION LAW</H3>

<PRE><I>Monday 16th &amp; Tuesday 17th September, OXFORD                       &#163;650.00</I></PRE><P>
In response to the requests of many delegates
at previous ESC conferences, this introductory course is planned
to be held in Oxford in the two days prior to the 1996 Anti-Trust
Law Conference.  The course will take the form of a series of
practical workshop sessions on the fundamental competition law
for those seeking an introduction or refresher course on the subject.
 Delegates may also opt to remain for the specialist Anti-Trust
Law event following on.<P>

<H3>15TH INTERNATIONAL ANTI-TRUST CONFERENCE</H3>

<PRE><I>18th - 20th September, OXFORD                               &#163;900.00</I></PRE><P>
Following on the theme of a truly international
event this conference, over three days looks at all aspects of
Anti-trust law. There will an  intemational round-up on the last
day.<P>

<H3>COMPETITION PROBLEMS IN MERGERS IN THE UK</H3>

<PRE><I>Tuesday 8th October, LONDON                         &#163;350.00</I></PRE><P>
As the European economy emerges from recession
and businesses exploit the Singe Market, cross-border mergers,
acquisitions or joint ventures will increase.  Lawyers and company
directors contemplating strategic commercial alliances need to
know the commission is intent on bringing merger control under
its wing with the 1996 Merger Regulation review.  This seminar
will examine the regulation in full, recent case law, what the
Commission's proposed changes are likely to be and how to deal
with them.<P>

<H3>19TH ANNUAL ADVANCED EC COMPETITION LAW CONFERENCE</H3>

<PRE><I>Tuesday 5th &amp; Wednesday 6th November, Brussels                        &#163;650.00</I></PRE><P>

This  two day conference offers a unique opportunity
for lawyers both in private practice and in industry to participate
in this update on recent developments in EC Competition Law. 
In addition to looking at the latest cases, regulations and other
changes in the area there will be the usual report from DGIV on
recent developments and proposals of the commission together with
the merger update forum discussion.

<P><HR><P><A HREF = "http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/onrnews.htm">Return to ONREUR newsletters</A> 
</BODY>

