<P>
<H2>Listing of some conferences to be held in Europe during remainder of 1996 that might be of interest to maritime industry management</H2>
<P>
Listed below is a selected list of conferences sponsored by various technical societies that might be of interest to management in the U.S. maritime industry.  For more information contact the organization found in each listing.  <P>	

[List prepared by Howard M. Bunch, Office of Naval Research Europe, 223 Old Marylebone Road, London NW1 5TH, England.  Tel: +44-171-514-4942. FAX: +44-171-723-6359. <BR>
e-mail: hbunch@onreur.navy.mil]
<P><HR><P>

<B>7th International Conference on Marine Engineering Systems:  Safe and Efficient Ships:  New Approaches for Design, Operation and Maintenance</B><BR>
Trondheim, Norway<BR>
<B>13-14 Jun 96</B><BR>
<I>Sponsor:</I>  International Cooperation on Marine Engineering Systems (ICMES), Institute of Marine Engineers (IMarE)<BR>
<I>Contact:</I>  Miss K. P. Ford, The Institute of Marine Engineers, Marine Management Holdings Ltd, The Memorial Building, 76 Mark Lane, London EC3R 7JN, United Kingdom, tel: 0171-488-1854, fax: 0171-481 8493<BR>
<I>Content:</I>  Focuses on the need for the shipping industry to enhance its standards of operation, particularly with regard to safety, efficiency, availability and environmental protection<BR>
