<HTML><HEAD><TITLE></TITLE></HEAD><BODY>
<CENTER><H2>Coastal Oceanography Report No. 4<BR>
Office of Naval Research Europe </H2>

<H3>20 October 1996</H3>

<H2>Summary of Results of a Workshop on International Collaboration in Nearshore Coastal  Research</H2>

<H3>Held in London, UK, on 17-18 October 1996<P>

Robert Dolan, ONR Europe; Thomas Kinder, ONR Coastal Dynamics; and
Lindwood Vincent, ONR Coastal Dynamics<P></CENTER>

<I>Keywords:  Inshore processes; sediment transport; bars and troughs; coastal field experiments; waves and current</I></H3>


<B>Introduction</B><P>

The Office of  Naval  Research hosted a two day workshop in London on 17 - 18 October, 1996, to explore potential international collaboration in research focused on nearshore coastal processes.  The motivations for the meeting was the desire of US and European research program managers to promote long-term international research, and to discuss the opportunity for support research under the new Naval International Collaborative Opportunity Program (NICOP).  The specific objective was to develop a framework for long-term initiatives, based on expansion of research underway within programs of excellence.  <P>

A decision was made to restrict the workshop to approximately 12 participants in order to facilitate discussion.  ONR selected the participants with a goal of inviting a broad cross-section of specialties in the field of coastal dynamics.<P>

<B>Participants</B><P>

