<P><H3>Office of Naval Research-European Office Biophysics<BR> 
Newsletter No. 5
</H3></P><P> <H3>Physics Conferences and Schools - 1995 and 1996</H3>
</P><P>Some time ago I sent you a list of "bio" conferences in Europe.
In this newsletter you will find a list of selected European conferences
in physics. (You probably can see that it will complete the term
"biophysics"). 
</P><P> The meetings are in date order divided into two categories -
Conferences and Schools -although the distinction between these
categories is not always evident. I did not try to use most of the
telephone and FAX numbers and also e-mail addresses mentioned in this
newsletter. 
</P><P> KEY TO ABBREVIATIONS:
</P><P> A: Application deadline <BR>  Ab: Abstracts deadline<BR> 
inv.: restricted to invited applicants<BR>  NP: no proceedings will be
published<BR>  P: Papers deadline (information on proceedings has not
been received)<BR>  PP: proceedings will be published (papers deadline)<BR>
  x: no. of participants ( c: contact (see address list)<BR>  lim.:
limited participation<BR>  +: country (area) tel. / fax email address;
WWW-http://
</P><P> INFORMATION IS FORMATTED AS:
</P><P> Date Title Place<BR>  Contact for information<BR>  A:
application deadline<BR>  PP or P: Papers deadline / Number of
participants / inv. / <BR>  languages other than English / conference
fee, Sponsor
</P><P></P><P>CONFERENCES 1995
