<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Biophysics Newsletter No. 10</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY><H3>August 25, 1995<BR>  European Biophysics<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/vodyanoy.htm">Igor Vodyanoy</A></H3>

<P><H3>Office of Naval Research-European Office Biophysics<BR> 
Newsletter No. 10
</H3></P><P> <H3>Sensory Biology and Biosensors Workshop-Review</H3>
</P><P>I am happy to transmit a letter from Dr. Felix Gribakin
announcing
</P><P><B>SENSORY BIOLOGY AND BIOSENSORS<BR>  Workshop-Review<BR> 
St. Petersburg<BR>  November 27-December 1, 1995</B><BR> 
</P><P><BR>  Nature has evolved extremely sensitive and versatile
sensory systems for detection of practically any minute change in
environmental trace chemicals, electromagnetic fields (and light),and
sound. It can combine extreme sensitivity with amplification and
selectivity.<BR> 
</P><P><BR>  The Chairman of the organizing committee of the Workshop-
Review "Sensory Biology And Biosensors" is honored to invite you to
participate in the SENSORY BIOLOGY AND BIOSENSORS workshop-review.
</P><P> The workshop will be held in St. Petersburg, Russia on November
27-December 1, 1995
</P><P> The main objective of the workshop is to exchange scientific
ideas and to review state-of-the-art Russian sensory biology and
biosensors science and technology.
</P><P> The review-workshop will allow US science managers to become
familiar with research progress in Russia, to discuss how the work can
be applied for development of man-made sensors, and to review the latest
accomplishments of Russian scientists in applied research in biosensors.
The workshop will be hosted by the Sechenov Institute of Evolutionary
Physiology & Biochemistry, Pavlov Institute of Physiology, and the
Russian Academy of Sciences and supported by the Russian Foundation for
Fundamental Research and by the Office of Naval Research Europe.
</P><P> To register please contact Dr. Sergej Kapitsky at:<BR> 
e-mail: kapitsky@ief.spb.su<BR>  or FAX: +7-812-552-3012
</P><P> In October-November please contact me as well at:<BR>  e-mail:
gribakin@ief.spb.suor <BR>  or FAX: +7-812-552-3012
</P><P> We will FAX you (with a copy sent to the Russian Embassy) an
invitation letter for your visa application. We will need your full
name, passport number and expiration date, your position and address,
birthday, and birthplace. We have to have your application before
September 15 in order to make reservations at the hotel.
</P><P> Preliminary Program:
</P><P><I>SENSORY BIOLOGY</I>
</P><P>
</P><OL>
<LI>Vision<BR>  Byzov - neural networks<BR>  Shevelev - vision
mechanisms<BR>  Ostrovsky- photoreceptors<BR>  Gribakin -
photoreception (insects)
<P>
</P></LI>
<LI>Hearing, Mechanoreception<BR>  Altman - perception (human, fish)<BR>
  Popov - perception (insects)<BR>  Akoev - mechanoreception<BR> 
