<HEAD>
<TITLE>Biophysics Newsletter No. 14</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY><H3>October 17, 1995<BR>  European Biophysics<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.ehis.navy.mil:80/vodyanoy.htm">Igor Vodyanoy</A></H3>

<P></P>
<H3>Office of Naval Research-European Office Biophysics<BR>
Newsletter No. 14 </H3> 
<P></P>
<H3>Science financed by Russians</H3> 
<P><B>Contents:</B></P><PRE> 
1. Summary
2. Russian Foundation For Basic Research (RFBR)
3. Glimpse of what is in the database
</PRE>
<P><B>1. SUMMARY</B><BR> 
</P><P> A complete list of all scientific projects funded in 1993-1994
by the Russian Foundation For Basic Research has been translated and is
available in <A HREF="rfbr9394.htm">electronic form</A>. The database
has the PI's name, project title, and the name and the address of the
respective institution. This is an excellent opportunity to review the
overall Basic Research Program in Russia. Collaboration from foreign
sources is invited.
</P><P><B>2. RUSSIAN FOUNDATION FOR BASIC RESEARCH (RFBR)</B><BR> 
</P><P>The Russian Foundation For Basic Research (RFBR) was established
by a Presidential Decree in 1992 as an independent federal agency for
the advancement of science in Russia. It receives and reviews research
proposals and awards individual, pilot and group grants, instrumentation
grants, support of data bases and information systems, and publication
projects. Their budget comes from the Federal Government as a fixed
share of the Federal budget for science. Additional funds are expected
to come from foreign sources through different cooperative and
collaborative projects. Thirty panels (10-16 experts each), from a pool
of about 1,000 scientists, review (for a fee) about 3,000 proposals
annually. RFBR presently supports about 1,200 institutions in the fields
of: Mathematics, computer and information sciences, physics, chemistry,
biology, geophysics, atmosphere, oceanography, humanities and arts. The
average grant is about $10,000/year.
</P><P><P><B>3. A GLIMPSE OF WHAT IS IN THE DATABASE</B><BR></P> 
<P><A HREF="rfbr9394.htm">RUSSIAN FOUNDATION FOR BASIC RESEARCH (RFBR)
INFORMATION BULLETIN N#2</A> Listing of selected scientific proposals
funded by RFBR after competitons in 1993 and 1994: </P></P><PRE>
Mathematics. Mechanics. Informatics.
Physics. Astronomy.
Chemistry.
Life Sciences.
Earth Sciences.
Economics. Social & Human Sciences.
Information Technologies. Data bases.
</PRE>
