<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Biophysics Newsletter No. 18</TITLE></HEAD>  
<BODY><H3>
March 8, 1996<BR>
European Biophysics<BR>
<A HREF="vodyanoy.htm">Igor Vodyanoy</A><P> 

Office Of Naval Research-European Office Biophysics<BR> 
Newsletter No. 18 <P> 

List of Research Projects from Armenia</H3> 
<P></P>
<PRE>
<B>Contents:</B>
1. Summary
2. About the List
3. Subject fields (key words)
4. Examples from the list
5. Projects from Armenia
</PRE>

<B>1. Summary:</B><P>
In November of 1995, a visit to Armenia was made jointly by 
scientists from the Office of Naval Research Europe and the 
European Office of Aerospace Research and Development. While 
visiting The Armenian Academy of Sciences, Armenian 
universities, and Research Institutions, we were offered a 
number of research proposals for future cooperation with 
scientists in the US. The list of these proposals is in this 
newsletter, compiled to be browsed electronically. Please, 
request from us any additional material on the project(s) 
relevant to your interests. Armenian scientists are looking 
forward to a future scientific exchange, collaboration and 
support. <P> 

<B>2. About the list:</B><P>
The list is numbered sequentially and consists of about 300 
entries. The information in each entry is partitioned by 
comas; the entry number is followed by a subject field, a 
researchers' name, a proposal title, an address of the 
institution and lastly by the number that was given to the 
proposal in the Armenian Academy's database.<P>

<B>3. Subject fields (Keywords):</B><P>
The following subject fields were used in the list: <BR>

Seismology, Geology, Geophysics,  Acoustics, Astronomy, 
Nuclear physics, Particle physics,  Physics,  Mathematical 
physics, Mathematics, ,  Plasma physics,  Plasma physics,  
X-ray optics, Optics, Nonlinear optics,  Imaging,  Liquid 
crystals,  Targeting, Thin films, Metrology, Free electron 
lasers,  Microwaves, Remote sensing,  
Electrodynamics, Electromagnetics,  Electronics, 
Environment, Solid state physics, Superconductivity,  
Computing, Control,  Materials,  Robotics,  Structures, 
Chemical physics, General and Inorganic Chemistry, Organic 
chemistry, Biochemistry,  Biophysics, Biosensors, 
Biotechnology, Botany,  Cardiology, Ecology,  Ecology, 
Hydroponics,  Medicine, Microbiology, Molecular Biology,  
Mycology,  Ecology,  Night vision,  Pharmacology,  
Physiology,  Radiation Medicine,  Economics.<P>

Some of the proposals could be placed into more 
than one subject field.<P>

