<H2>List of titles since November 1992 (starting with the most recent one):</H2><P><HR>
<H3>Newsletter #52<BR>
Bulk GaN crystals produced in Poland<BR>
16-June-95</H3>
<B>Content:</B>

<OL>
<LI>Preface
<LI>Yes we grow bulk GaN, but .....<BR>
- Growth conditions<BR>
- Some data on bulk and homoepitaxial layers<BR>
- Related activities<BR>
<LI>Availability of samples
<LI>Author's comments
<LI>Other high pressure R&D activities at HPRC<BR>
- Biological systems under high pressure<BR>
- DNA manipulation and bio-engineering<BR>
- Synthesis of non-porous alumina<BR>
<LI>Recent GaN related publications from HPRC
<LI>Contacts
</OL>
 
<B>Abstract</B><BR>
This newsletter reports on a recent (early June 1995) trip by the author to the High Pressure Research Center (HPRC) of the Polish Academy of Sciences (also known as UNIPRESS) in Warsaw. It assesses the current status of their bulk crystal growth of GaN, a material which is of utmost importance to the development of blue emitting laser diodes. The Polish grown GaN crystal are the ONLY KNOWN BULK GaN IN EXISTENCE IN THE WORLD. Some interesting findings include:

<UL>
<LI>The largest GaN crystal platelet grown is about 8 mm
<LI>The institute is scaling up the process
<LI>Homoepitaxial GaN has been grown on these materials
<LI>X-ray rocking curve measurements indicate good crystalline material; TEM show atomically flat surface
<LI>The bulk GaN is transparent, n-type, and highly conductive
<LI>Sample distribution is tightly controlled
<LI>High purity AlN, GaN, and InN powders are also produced at HPRC
</UL>

<P><HR>
<H3>Newsletter #51<BR>
Electronics R&D in Italy<BR>
5-May-95</H3>
<B>Content:</B>

<OL>
<LI>Organizational overview of Italian Electronics R&D<BR>
- Excellence in education<BR>
- Research approach & limitations<BR>
- The National Research Council institutes<BR>
- Industrial connection<BR>
<LI>MASPEC - Electronic & Magnetic Materials institute<BR>
- Buffer layer engineering<BR>
<LI>University of Parma - Department of Information Technology<BR>
- Locus for interdisciplinary and interdepartmental research<BR>
- Center of excellence in device reliability<BR>
<LI>University of Padova - Department of Electronics and Informatics  
<LI>Comments
<LI>Contacts
</OL>

<B>Abstract</B><BR>

This article gives an overview on electronics R&D in Italy; how it is funded and organized. It focuses on the research efforts at three major institutions: (1) Materiali Speciali per Elettronica e Magnetismo (MASPEC) or Special Materials for Electronics and Magnetism, (2) the Department of Information Technology, Engineering Faculty, University of Parma, and (3) the Department of Electronics and Informatics at the University of Padova. Emphasis is on semiconductor materials research and device reliability in silicon and III-V based semiconductors. The report is based on site visit in April 1995.
<P><HR>
