<H3>Newsletter #47<BR>
News from Brussels - <BR>
EU Fourth Framework Program for R&D (1994-98)<BR>
9-Feb-95</H3>
<B>Content:</B>

<OL>
<LI>Information & communication
<LI>Industrial technology
<LI>Environment
<LI>Energy
<LI>International cooperation
<LI>Dissemination and exploitation of results
<LI>Training and mobility of researchers
<LI>Budget (Table)
<LI>Contacts
</OL>

<B>Abstract</B><BR>
The European Unions's Fourth Framework Program for Research and Technological Development - which has a budget of ECU 12.3B (about $15B) to spend on 18 R&D programs between 1994 and 1998 finally swung into action on 15 December 1994. Eight programs launched calls for proposals, and another nine issued "advance notices", which included the full text of calls due to be launched this month. Further calls for proposals will be issued on March 15, June 15, September 15 and December 15. Brief details, including contact information, of all the programs relevant to physicists & engineers are given below. Table lists programs and their budgets. For on overview on Framework Program and a graphic hierarchical guide to the European Community's programs in S&T see Newsletter #29  on Electronics.<P>
