<HEAD>
<TITLE>Newsletter #61 on electronics: Technology Assessment: European Electronics</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H3>ONR Europe S&amp;T Reports <BR>
London, UK</H3>
<HR>
<P>
<H3>ONREUR 96-1-R
<P>
Technology Assessment: European Electronics
<P>
Nicholas Bottka<P>
Office of Naval Research, European Office<BR>
London, UK<P>

March 6, 1996</H3><P>

<H3>Published by:<P>
Office of Naval Research European Office<BR>
223 Old Marylebone Street, London NW1 5TH, UK<BR>
Tel: +44(71)514-4260, Fax: +44(71)723-6359 London<BR>
Tel: (703)696-4961, Fax: (703)696-2611 in Arlington<BR>
Author's current e-mail: bottkan@onrhq.onr.navy.mil<P>
<HR><P>
Approved for public release, distribution
unlimited</H3><P><HR><P>

<P>
<CENTER><B>Abstract<BR>
</B></CENTER>
<P>
The author, who represented the Office of Naval Research in London
as a liaison scientist from 1992 to 1995, presents an in-depth
technical assessment of electronic R&amp;D in Europe. The report
covers topics in electronics, which are of interest to ONR,  the
US defense establishment, and the general S&amp;T community. He
has focussed on activities in solid state and vacuum electronics
R&amp;D in the various regions in Europe, with emphasis on Germany
and the Former Soviet Union.  Observations are based on his personal
visits to leading R&amp;D institutions in Europe and his interaction
with scientists, engineers, and S&amp;T managers throughout Europe.
 Topics covered include design, processing, measurement methodology,
 and manufacturing of electronic components. The report explores
business strategy, as well as the driving forces behind European
electronic S&amp;T development. The most recent technological
breakthroughs in MMICs and optoelectronic ICs are highlighted,
and the European approach to monolithic microwave IC development
is compared to current US activities in this field. The author
comments upon the impact of the new economic and political reality
in central and eastern Europe on electronic S&amp;T, presenting
assessments and recommendations when warranted.<BR>

<P>
<HR>
<P>
<I>Keywords: Assessment; research programs; MMIC; lasers; semiconductors;
devices; measurements</I>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
ONREUR report Draft - Final (6 March 1996)
<P>
Latest update: 6 March 1996
<P>
File name: Final.doc (e-mail version, PC MS Word 6.0)
<P>
<HR>
<P>
